# QA Verification Gate

No commit until all checks pass. This exists because the #1 cause of wasted time is declaring changes done without verification.

## When To Run
- After any CSS, HTML, or JS change to dashboard.html
- After modifying any Flask route or API endpoint
- Before every git commit

## Check 1 — Flask Server Health
curl -s -o /dev/null -w "%{http_code}" http://localhost:5001/dashboard
PASS = HTTP 200. FAIL = stop, do not proceed.

## Check 2 — API Endpoint Health
Curl every known endpoint. Must return HTTP 200 and valid JSON.
– /api/ash/inbox (required fields: action_type, description, timestamp)
- /api/ash/inbox/stats (required: today, yesterday, total)
- /api/ash/activity (required: action_type, description, timestamp)
- /api/ash/weekly (required: data for current week)
- /api/ash/status
- /api/bookkeeping (optional — skip if 404)

If field names do not match what JS expects, FAIL immediately.

## Check 3 — JavaScript Syntax
Extract all script blocks from templates/dashboard.html and run node --check.
PASS = exit code 0. FAIL = report exact error and line number.

## Check 4 — Visual Verification (Manual)
- 4a: Check browser console for red errors
- 4b: Measure affected elements if CSS changed
- 4c: Click through every nav tab after HTML structure changes

## Rules
1. NEVER skip checks, even if change seems trivial
2. NEVER allow commit if any check shows FAIL
3. NEVER use Playwright, Puppeteer, or headless browsers
4. NEVER say looks good based on reading code — run actual checks
